definition.value: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of haloxyfop-P-sodium and its enantiomer, (S)-haloxyfop-sodium. It is a post-emergence herbicide for the control annual and perennial grass weeds.
An organic sodium salt resulting from the formal reaction of haloxyfop-P with 1 mol eq. of sodium hydride.

An organic sodium salt resulting from the formal reaction of (S)-haloxyfop with 1 mol eq. of sodium hydride. The agrochemical herbicide haloxyfop-sodium is an equimolar mixture of (S)-haloxyfop-sodium and its enantiomer.
A steroidal acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate functions of 3-oxochenodeoxycholoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A sulfonium compound that is S-adenosyl-L-methionine in which one of the methyl hydrogens has been replaced by a carboxy group.
A tetrachlorobiphenyl that is biphenyl in which the hydrogens at position 3 and 4 on each phenyl group are replaced by chlorines.
A steroidal acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate functions of 3-oxocholoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A steroidal acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate functions of 3-oxodeoxycholoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

A member of the class of azetidines that is melagatran in which the carboxylic acid group has been converted into the corresponding ethyl ester and in which the amidine group has been converted to the corresponding hydroxylamine. Tautomeric with the oxime form of ximelagatran.
A steroidal acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate functions of 3-oxolithocholoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-(fatty acyl)-L-alpha-amino acid anion that is the conjugate base of N-propanoyl-L-methionine, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

An oligopeptide composed of L-glutamine, L-tyrosine, L-isoleucine, L-lysine, L-alanine, L-asparagine, L-serine, L-lysine, L-phenylalanine, L-isoleucine, glycine, L-isoleucine, L-threonine, L-glutamic acid and L-leucine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.

An oligopeptide composed of L-proline, L-arginine, L-tyrosine, L-valine, L-lysine, L-glutamine, L-asparagine, L-threonine, L-leucine, L-lysine, L-leucine, L-alanine and L-threonine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-mannosyl-L-serine.

An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-6-O-phosphono-alpha-D-mannosyl-L-serine residue
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-mannosyl-L-threonine.

An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-6-O-phosphono-alpha-D-mannosyl-L-threonine residue
An L-isoleucine derivative resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of oleic acid with the amino group of L-isoleucine.
A short chain fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of pivaloyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A fatty amide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of oleic acid with the amino group of L-glutamic acid.
An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy groups of C-terminal-gamma-(L-glutamyl)-L-2-glutamic acid group. Major structure at pH 7.3.

An oligopeptide composed of L-asparagine, L-proline, L-valine, L-valine, L-histidine, L-phenylalanine, L-phenylalanine, L-lysine, L-asparagine, L-isoleucine, L-valine, L-threonine, L-proline, L-arginine, L-threonine, L-proline, L-proline, L-proline and L-serine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
The conjugate base of a N-fatty-acyl-L-alpha-amino acid arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate groups of C-terminal-gamma-(5-phospho-L-glutamyl)-L-2-glutamic acid group. Major structure at pH 7.3.
A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from deprotonation of the carboxy group of (S)-haloxyfop.
The methyl ester of 2-(4-{[3-chloro-5-(trifluoromethyl)pyridin-2-yl]oxy}phenoxy)propanoic acid.
An N-acyl-L-aspartic acid in which the acyl group is specified as 2-oxindole-3-acetyl.

A polysaccharide derivative comprising a tetrasaccharide repeating unit consisting of beta-D-glucose, beta-D-galactose, beta-D-glucuronic acid and beta-D-glucose residues all linked sequentially (1->4) and with the tetrasaccharide repeats themselves being linked (1->4); corresponds to the serotype 8 capsular polysaccharide (CPS) of Streptococcus pneumoniae.
A trihydroxy-5beta-cholanic acid in which the three hydroxy groups are located at positions 1beta, 3alpha, and 12alpha.

A beta-D-glucoside that is the 5-aminopentyl glycoside of a tetrasaccharide consisting of beta-D-glucosyl, beta-D-galactosyl, beta-D-glucuronosyl and beta-D-glucosyl residues linked sequentially (1->4).

A beta-D-glucoside that is the 2-azidoethyl glycoside of a tetrasaccharide (Streptococcus pneumoniae serotype 3 tetrasaccharide) consisting of two beta-D-glucuronosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl disaccharide units linked (1->3).
A member of the class of furans obtained by reduction of the 5-nitro group of nitrofurazone to the corresponding hydroxylamine.

A beta-D-glucoside that is the 2-azidoethyl glycoside of a tetrasaccharide (Streptococcus pneumoniae serotype 14 tetrasaccharide) consisting of at the reducing end an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue to which are linked (1->4) and (1->6) respectively a beta-D-glucose residue and a beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl disaccharide unit.

A methyl 2-(4-{[3-chloro-5-(trifluoromethyl)pyridin-2-yl]oxy}phenoxy)propanoate that has R configuration. It is a proherbicide (by hydrolysis of the methyl ester) for the herbicide haloxyfop-P, the most active enantiomer of the racemic herbicide haloxyfop.
An all-trans-4-hydroxyretinoic acid in which the 4-hydroxy group has S-configuration.
A pyrimidine deoxyribonucleotide(1-) residue obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 5-hydroxymethyldeoxycytidine 5'-monophosphate residue.
A methyl 2-(4-{[3-chloro-5-(trifluoromethyl)pyridin-2-yl]oxy}phenoxy)propanoate that has S configuration. It is the (much less active) enantiomer of the proherbicide haloxyfop-P-methyl.
A benzylisoquinoline alkaloid that is (R)-tetrahydropapaverine in which the amino hydrogen has been replaced by a methyl group
The R-enantiomer of tetrahydropapaverine.

A carboxylic ester that is the resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2-(4-{[3-chloro-5-(trifluoromethyl)pyridin-2-yl]oxy}phenoxy)propanoic acid with the hydroxy group of 2-ethoxyethanol.
A 2-ethoxyethyl 2-(4-{[3-chloro-5-(trifluoromethyl)pyridin-2-yl]oxy}phenoxy)propanoate that has R configuration.
A 2-ethoxyethyl 2-(4-{[3-chloro-5-(trifluoromethyl)pyridin-2-yl]oxy}phenoxy)propanoate that has S configuration.

A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of haloxyfop-P-etotyl and its less active enantiomer, (S)-haloxyfop-etotyl. It is a proherbicide (by ester hydrolysis to give the corresponding carboxylic acid) used to control annual and perennial grass weeds.

An alpha-D-glucoside that is the 5-aminopentyl glycoside of a tetrasaccharide consisting of alpha-D-galactosyl, beta-D-glucuronosyl, beta-D-glucosyl and alpha-D-glucosyl residues linked sequentially (1->4).

An alpha-D-galactoside that is the 5-aminopentyl glycoside of a tetrasaccharide consisting of beta-D-glucuronosyl, beta-D-glucosyl,  alpha-D-glucosyl and alpha-D-galactosyl residues linked sequentially (1->4).

A carbohydrate acid derivative anion that is the conjugate base of 2-O-[alpha-D-glucosyl-(1->6)-alpha-D-glucosyl]-D-glyceric acid arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

A carbohydrate acid derivative anion that is the conjugate base of 2-O-[6-O-octanoyl-alpha-D-glucosyl-(1->6)-alpha-D-glucosyl]-D-glyceric acid arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

A beta-D-glucoside that is the 5-aminopentyl glycoside of a tetrasaccharide consisting of beta-D-glucosyl, alpha-D-glucosyl, beta-D-glucuronosyl and alpha-D-galactosyl residues linked sequentially (1->4).

An alpha-D-galactoside that is the 2-aminoethyl glycoside of a tetrasaccharide consisting of beta-D-glucuronosyl, beta-D-glucosyl, alpha-D-glucosyl and alpha-D-galactosyl residues linked sequentially (1->4).
